Create a Google Apps Script function to generate a chart from lab data in Google Sheets with the following features:

- The script should first try to find a sheet named "LabData"
- If the sheet does not exist, it should automatically use the currently active sheet
- The script should dynamically detect the last row of data instead of using a fixed range
- Assume the first two columns contain the data (X and Y values)
- The first row contains headers
- If there is not enough data (less than 2 rows), throw an error

Chart requirements:
- Create a line chart
- Set chart title as "Absorbance vs Time"
- X-axis title: "Time (min)"
- Y-axis title: "Absorbance"
- Place the chart below the data automatically
- Remove any existing charts before creating a new one

Bonus:
- Add a Logger message if the "LabData" sheet is not found
- Make the code clean, readable, and beginner-friendly

Return only the Apps Script code.
